onic/stereo).'), Entity(name='Coltrane In Japan', type='Work', importance=0.5, isolated_context='The 4-CD set compiles all the music issued as three albums in the seventies by Impulse! ; "Coltrane In Japan" (1974, Japan 3-LP (side six is blank), mono).'), Entity(name='Second Night In Tokyo', type='Work', importance=0.5, isolated_context='The 4-CD set compiles all the music issued as three albums in the seventies by Impulse! ; "Second Night In Tokyo" (1976, Japan 3-LP (side six contains an interview, mono).'), Entity(name='Coltrane In Tokyo Vol. 1', type='Work', importance=0.5, isolated_context='The US 4-CD edition includes both of these volumes, with identical mastering from the original mono tapes. The first CD issues were by Impulse! Japan as two 2-CD sets: "Live In Japan Vol. 1" (same as "Coltrane In Japan") and "Live In Japan Vol. 2" (same as "Second Night In Tokyo").'), Entity(name='Coltrane In Tokyo Vol. 2', type='Work', importance=0.5, isolated_context='The US 4-CD edition includes both of these volumes, with identical mastering from the original mono tapes. The first CD issues were by Impulse! Japan as two 2-CD sets: "Live In Japan Vol. 1" (same as "Coltrane In Japan") and "Live In Japan Vol. 2" (same as "Second Night In Tokyo").'), Entity(name='MCA', type='Organization', importance=0.5, isolated_context='The US 4-CD edition includes both of these volumes, with identical mastering from the original mono tapes. The side six interview from "Second Night In Tokyo" has never been reissued on any CD edition.')] concepts=[Concept(name='Jazz Music', definition='', isolated_context=''), Concept(name='Live Album', definition='', isolated_context=''), Concept(name='Box Set', definition='', isolated_context='')] tasks=[] persona_traits=[] references=[ExternalReference(title='Live in Japan', type='Album', content='', source='John Coltrane', isolated_context='Live in Japan is a four-disc box set by American saxophonist John Coltrane and his last group, featuring the quin